  "texts": [
    "This highlights the need to expand and refine the training dataset to improve the model's generalization across a wider range of foraminiferan species.",
    "Amao (2021) automate the taxonomic search of benthic Foraminifera using CNNs, successfully achieving this aim despite limitations imposed by a small dataset size.",
    "Hsiang et al. (2019) automate the taxonomic identification of planktonic Foraminifera using CNNs trained using a large dataset of over 34,000 images.",
    "They applied several modifications to the standard VGG16, including the use of a 160x160 pixel image size, different dropout regularizations, and a self-adjusting learning rate.",
    "This approach demonstrated high accuracies, rivaling human experts, and marked a significant leap in species-level fossil classification."
